Class EndpointRegistrationInfoResponse

  • java.lang.Object
    • ch.ecma.csta.CastorObject
      • com.avaya.csta.binding.EndpointRegistrationInfoResponse
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable

    public class EndpointRegistrationInfoResponse
extends ch.ecma.csta.CastorObject
implements java.io.Serializable
    Response to the EndpointRegistrationInfoRequest.
    EndpointRegistrationInfoResponse Parameters
    device SubjectDeviceID Specifies the DeviceID for which information was requested. Extracting the device ID is a two-step process: 
      SubjectDeviceID subjDeviceID = event.getDevice();
  DeviceID deviceID = subjDeviceID.getDeviceIdentifier();
    Mandatory.
    serviceState ServiceState The current state of the station - inService, outOfService or unknown. Provided when available.
    endpointRegistrationInfo EndpointRegistrationInfo Holds at most four EndpointRegistrationInfo objects, each corresponding to an endpoint that is registered against the station. Mandatory.
    Version:
    $Revision$ $Date$
    See Also:
    Serialized Form
